---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Window Replacement Narre Warren | Aluminium, Double-Glaze, Sliders | (03) 9003 0108"
  description="Window and sliding-door replacement in Narre Warren and Narre Warren South. 1990s–2000s brick-veneer re-window jobs, double-glaze upgrades, sliding-door upsizing for indoor-outdoor flow."
  canonical="https://berwickwindowreplacement.com.au/narre-warren/">

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Narre Warren &middot; Narre Warren South &middot; Narre Warren North</span>
      <h1>Window replacement in <span class="accent">Narre Warren</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Narre Warren is the original Berwick growth corridor &mdash; bulk-built
        through the late 80s, 90s and early 2000s. Almost every house in the
        suburb has the same builder-spec single-glaze aluminium frames from
        that era, and they&rsquo;re hitting the 25&ndash;35 year mark all at
        once: chalky white powder coat, perimeter sealant cracking, winter
        condensation streaks, and slider rollers that scrape or seize.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book a free measure</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Why Narre Warren</span>
      <h2>The Narre Warren window story.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">
        <h3>The 90s aluminium wave is up for renewal.</h3>
        <p>
          Narre Warren and Narre Warren South estates &mdash; Casey Fields,
          Fountain Gate-adjacent, Strathaird, the Amberley Park belt &mdash;
          were built out from the mid 80s through to around 2005, almost
          entirely with single-glaze aluminium framing. That stock is now
          25&ndash;40 years old, and the symptoms are textbook: condensation
          on every window in July, mould creeping up the architraves,
          sliders that don&rsquo;t close flush against the jamb, double-hung
          windows where the friction stays gave out. Full frame replacement
          is the right call &mdash; glass-only doesn&rsquo;t fix the failed
          seals or the worn hardware.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Double-glaze upgrade pays for itself.</h3>
        <p>
          On a typical 4-bed Narre Warren home with 13 windows + a back
          slider, the single-glaze re-window lands around $13K&ndash;$15K.
          Adding double-glazing across the lot lifts that to $17K&ndash;$20K.
          The $4K&ndash;$5K premium typically pays back in 8&ndash;12 years
          through reduced heating and cooling, and it&rsquo;s instant relief
          on the winter condensation problem &mdash; cold-side surface
          temperature lifts from ~5&deg;C to ~14&deg;C, well above the
          dew point so condensation just stops forming.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Indoor-outdoor sliding door upgrades.</h3>
        <p>
          The Narre Warren standard-spec 2.4m rear sliding door from a
          90s build looks small by current taste. We do a lot of upgrades
          here: punch the opening wider, install a 3.6m stacker (three
          panels, two stack behind one fixed) for $4.5K&ndash;$6.5K, or
          a full bifold across 4&ndash;5 panels for $7K&ndash;$10K if the
          owner wants the opening to disappear completely.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Typical Narre Warren jobs.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Full-house re-window, 12&ndash;14 windows, single-glaze ($12K&ndash;$15K)</li>
          <li>Same job with double-glaze upgrade ($16K&ndash;$20K)</li>
          <li>2.4m rear slider replacement, like-for-like ($2.5K&ndash;$4K)</li>
          <li>2.4m &rarr; 3.6m stacker upgrade with opening widening ($5K&ndash;$8K)</li>
          <li>Kitchen + 2 bathroom awning swap-out ($1.8K&ndash;$3.2K)</li>
          <li>Front-of-house window replacement only (curb-appeal job) ($4K&ndash;$8K)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Other service areas.</h2>
      <div class="areas-grid">
        <a class="area-pill" href="/berwick/">Berwick</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/cranbourne/">Cranbourne</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/hampton-park/">Hampton Park</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/endeavour-hills/">Endeavour Hills</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/city-of-casey/">All City of Casey</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>Free Narre Warren window measure-up.</h2>
        <p>Most 90s-era homes here are full re-window candidates. Single vs double-glaze priced both ways.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book online</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
